title: control [Marburg]
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from 200 μl of plasma using the miRCURY RNA isolation kit-biofluid (Exiqon) according to the manufacturer’s protocol
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Next Generation Sequencing process for biofluids microRNA and small RNA sequencing at Exiqon.
data_processing: Total RNA was extracted from 200 μl of plasma using the miRCURY RNA isolation kit for biofluids (Exiqon).
data_processing.1: Purified RNA was eluted in 50 μl RNAase free water. Total RNA was extracted using miRCURY RNA isolation kit and small RNA libraries were generated using NEBNEXT library generation kit (New England Biolabs Inc.).
data_processing.2: Samples were sequenced on the Illumina system by Exiqon Services, Denmark.
data_processing.3: Intensity correction, base calling and assigning of Q-scores were then performed as part of measures to assess the quality of the data obtained.
data_processing.4: Differential expression analysis was performed using the EdgeR statistical software package.
